=
Let $cal(S)$ be an inertial reference system. Use Galileo's velocity addition
rule.

(a) Suppose that $ol(cal(S))$ moves with constant velocity relative to $cal(S)$. Show that $ol(cal(S))$ is also an inertial reference system. [Hint: Use the definition in footnote 1.]

(b) Conversely, show that if $ol(cal(S))$ is an inertial system, then it moves with respect to $cal(S)$
at constant velocity.